windows.question:
Which of the following best describes the anomaly detection results within the time series window spanning steps 643 to 662?
A) Sudden Decrease anomaly: Values experience a rapid decline that fails to match nearby gradual behavior.
B) Upward Spike anomaly: There is a sharp upward jump in the measurements.
C) The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.

options.A: Sudden Decrease anomaly: Values experience a rapid decline that fails to match nearby gradual behavior.
options.B: Upward Spike anomaly: There is a sharp upward jump in the measurements.
options.C: The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.

windows.answer: B) Upward Spike anomaly: There is a sharp upward jump in the measurements.
